parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to be difficult to stop, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the brakes are difficult to push
the vehicle is hard to stop
especially when backing out of a garage or traveling uphill.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature wear of rear brake pads can cause the rotors to become damaged, leading to unsafe braking conditions and potentially resulting in accidents.
